Package: ggloop
Type: Package
Title: A looper for ggplot2
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Author@R: person("Luke", "Smith", email = "luke@protocolvital.info",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
URL: https://github.com/seasmith/ggloop
BugReports: https://github.com/seasmith/ggloop/issues
Description: Pass a data frame and mapping aesthetics to ggloop() in order
    to create a list of ggplot object for the specified remapping of aesthetics.
    Pass x, y, and ... aesthetics to ggloop as you would with ggplot. You can
    add geoms and other features to these objects with the special %L+% (l-plus)
    operator.
License: GPL-2
LazyData: TRUE
Imports:
    dplyr,
    ggplot2,
    magrittr
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
